<section>

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<p>
Whale Protocol Official (WPO) is an independent community initiative dedicated to strengthening integrity and transparency within digital asset markets through structured reporting, evidence-based analysis, and responsible risk alerts.
WPO does not provide financial advice or price predictions. It operates as a community-driven integrity layer designed to reduce risk and restore trust in digital markets.
</p>

<h2>2. Market Problem</h2>
<ul>
<li>Fraudulent or misleading projects</li>
<li>Wallets linked to scam activity</li>
<li>Coordinated price manipulation</li>
<li>Unlocked liquidity risks</li>
<li>Dangerous smart contract privileges</li>
<li>Unfair token distributions</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Mission & Vision</h2>
<h3>Mission</h3>
<p>Build a transparent, evidence-based reporting system that reduces risk and supports investor protection.</p>

<h3>Vision</h3>
<p>Become a recognized integrity layer strengthening digital markets through transparency and accountability.</p>

<h2>4. Platform Architecture</h2>
<ul>
<li>Report Submission Interface</li>
<li>Evidence Review Layer</li>
<li>Risk Classification Engine</li>
<li>Public Report Archive</li>
<li>WPO Token Utility Layer</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. How the Protocol Works</h2>
<h3>Step 1 ‚Äì Report Submission</h3>
<ul>
<li>Transaction Hashes (TX)</li>
<li>Wallet Addresses</li>
<li>Explorer Links</li>
<li>Timeline Description</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 2 ‚Äì Evidence Review</h3>
<p>Liquidity status, contract ownership, token distribution, and suspicious activity patterns are analyzed.</p>

<h3>Step 3 ‚Äì Risk Classification</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>HIGH</strong> ‚Äì Elevated risk indicators</li>
<li><strong>MEDIUM</strong> ‚Äì Further verification required</li>
<li><strong>INFO</strong> ‚Äì General safety reminder</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 4 ‚Äì Public Alert</h3>
<p>Neutral, evidence-based reports are published without defamatory claims.</p>

<h2>6. Coordinated Action Framework</h2>
<p>
When strong evidence of harmful activity is identified, documented case files may be prepared and shared with relevant compliance or technical teams.
Whale Protocol does not possess enforcement authority.
</p>

<h2>7. WPO Token Overview</h2>
<p><strong>Total Supply: 7,500,000 WPO</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Fixed supply</li>
<li>No minting</li>
<li>No burn mechanism</li>
<li>Non-inflationary</li>
</ul>

<h2>8. Token Allocation</h2>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Category</th>
<th>Percentage</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Circulating Supply</td>
<td>60%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Locked Strategic Reserve</td>
<td>40%</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>9. Token Utility Model</h2>

<h3>Stake-Based Reporting</h3>
<p>
Users stake WPO tokens when submitting a report. Tokens remain locked during review.
Validated reports may receive rewards. Unsupported reports may face partial deductions.
</p>

<h3>Instant Fee Model</h3>
<p>
Reports may also be submitted through a direct WPO fee. Fees are transferred to the protocol treasury and are non-refundable.
</p>

<h2>10. Governance</h2>
<p>1 WPO = 1 Vote</p>
<ul>
<li>Reporting fee adjustments</li>
<li>Risk classification updates</li>
<li>Supported network expansion</li>
<li>Reward policy decisions</li>
</ul>

<h2>11. Roadmap</h2>
<ul>
<li>Website & reporting system launch</li>
<li>Stake-based reporting activation</li>
<li>Advanced analytics dashboard</li>
<li>Community governance rollout</li>
</ul>

<h2>12. Security & Integrity Policy</h2>
<ul>
<li>No accusations without evidence</li>
<li>No personal data publication</li>
<li>No financial advice</li>
<li>No price speculation</li>
</ul>

<h2>13. Legal Disclaimer</h2>
<p>
Whale Protocol Official is not a regulatory authority and does not provide financial or legal advice.
All reports are published for educational and risk-awareness purposes only.
</p>

